About the job
Are you ready for your business analysis journey? Are you motivated by challenges, variety, and learning? If you are a young and motivated working student who wants to start a career in CIO Advisory, Business & Data Analysis, we have the right position for you! We are hiring an Intern or Working Student with a focus on Business & Data Analysis to join our project team in Munich. You will report directly to the project manager and will support a number of projects with varying degrees of complexity. The duration of the internship is 3 months with a possibility of extension.

What Will You Do

Analyze large, unstructured, and complex financial data sets identifying data anomalies, issues, and approaches to resolve discrepancies;
Participate in cross-functional working group sessions to translate business requirements into system specifications;
Assist with the functional documentation of customer business requirements Conduct user acceptance testing and support investigation of questions, issues, and defects;
Ensure compliance with policies, standards, and regulatory requirements Managing the production of deliverables to time, cost and quality requirements;
Managing the expectations and satisfaction of the project’s sponsor and stakeholders.

What Will Help You To Fulfill Your Role

A university degree (or running study) in an analytical field – e.g. Economics, Engineering, Business, Mathematics, Statistics, Finance or related field;
Exceptional analytical and conceptual thinking skills;
Ability to work effectively with management and part of a team to meet targets;
Ability to influence stakeholders and work closely with them to determine acceptable solutions;
Strong attention to detail;
Good communication skills both in written and verbal;
Experience in one analytical programming language like SQL, SAS, Python, or similar is preferred;
Business proficiency in English and German. Proficiency in Italian is desirable;
Competency in Microsoft applications including Word, Excel, Powerpoint, and Outlook.

What We Offer

A multitude of demanding projects in an international context;
A flat hierarchy, which will not be tied up in politics;
Professional in-house training programs, including “on the job”, constructive feedback and coaching;
Autonomy in your day-to-day processes.

